<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-145-083 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 881 286</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX World  June 1991 v8 n6 p111(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Low-cost publishing for the masses. (Software Review) (Elan'sAvalon Publisher) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Edwards, Keith.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Avalon Publisher 1.1, $995, from Elan Computer Group is anexpensive desktop publishing product for UNIX users; it is not forpeople new to computing.andP;  It can compete against FrameMaker andInterleaf on a price basis, but the other programs offer morefunctions and flexibility than Avalon does.andP;  Avalon's strengthsare that it is easy to use, inexpensive, and has interfaceconsistency.andP;  There are 36 fonts.andP;  Users can specify spacingparameters.andP;  The program can operate on entire pages.andP;  Thedisadvantages are that only basic graphics tools are provided,there is little support for mathematical equations, and it isawkward to do the table of contents and index.andP;  It runs underOpenWindows and complies with OpenWindows-style guidelines.andP;  Usersnew to desktop publishing or users with simple desktop needsshould consider Avalon Publisher.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Elan Computer Group Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Avalon Publisher 1.1 (Desktop publishing software).andO;Topic:     Desktop PublishingEvaluationSoftware Packages.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Review highlights: Avalon Publisher. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>